Source: QuaRTz (Qualitative Relationship Test set) (Dataset - https://allenai.org/data/quartz) (Paper - https://aclanthology.org/D19-1608.pdf)
Definition: You are given a question or blank (Question), two answer options (Option1 and Option2) and a Qualitative Statement. Your task is to find the correct answer for the given question from the given options and using Qualitative Statement.

Positive Examples.input: Question: The government of Canada is considering implementing less carbon taxes across the country. If these taxes were implemented, the amount of carbon dioxide emissions in the country would be expected to Option1: fall Option2: rise Qualitative Statement: The carbon taxes encourage people to use less fossil fuel, which reduces carbon dioxide emissions.
Positive Examples.explanation: As mentioned in the Qualitative Statement, due to taxes people will reduce usage of fossil fuel and hence, carbon dioxide emission will also reduce. So, if Camada government decrease the tax, people will use it more and hencce, emission will also incerase.

Positive Examples.input: Question: Shampoos with high ph are Option1: less acidic Option2: more or Qualitative Statement: Lower pH numbers are more acidic and higher numbers are less acidic (also called more alkaline).
Positive Examples.explanation: As mentioned in the Qualitative Statement, high pH indictes more acidic. Hence, Shampoos with high Ph are more acidic.

Positive Examples.input: Question: If an object starts speeding up, it is encountering _____ friction against it. Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: The smoother the surface, the less friction against an object, so the faster it will move.
Positive Examples.explanation: As mentioned in the Qualitative Statement, smooth surface ha sless friction. Hence, if an object moves fast, it encounters less friction.

Question: When nobody in a country can afford a car do they use more or less energy? Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: People in the richer nations of the world use far more energy, especially energy from fossil fuels, than people in the poorer nations do.

Question: If valence electrons are far from an atom's nucleus, the atom is likely Option1: bigger Option2: smaller Qualitative Statement: In bigger atoms, valence electrons are farther from the nucleus.

Question: What happens to the size of a population if the number of predators for that population is increased? Option1: gets bigger Option2: gets smaller Qualitative Statement: An increase in predators, the emergence of a new disease, or the loss of habitat are just three possible problems that will decrease a population.

Question: The elephants were moved to a reservation where they could thrive, since their habitat in the wild had expanded too far. The elephant numbers were now Option1: larger Option2: smaller Qualitative Statement: The forest habitat of elephants has also decreased in size due to humans moving in, so the numbers of the elephants have decreased.

Question: Sandra is walking down a sunny street and then suddenly goes into a dark building. Sarah's pupils will do this in response to the new low light Option1: shrink Option2: grow Qualitative Statement: The pupil automatically gets bigger or smaller to let more or less light in as needed.

Question: Dave dropped a feather and a ball out of a window. The ball landed first because it had mass that, compared to the feather, was Option1: greater Option2: lesser Qualitative Statement: The greater the objects mass, the greater the force of attraction; in addition, the greater the distance between objects, the smaller the force of attraction.

Question: If Mona wants to clear her farm land at a faster rate, what would adding people do to that rate? Option1: increase it Option2: decrease it Qualitative Statement: More people also means more clearing of land for agriculture and development.

Question: Dana goes with her mother to get screened for breast cancer. The person who is less likely to have it has an age that is Option1: higher Option2: lower Qualitative Statement: Breast cancer is rare in teens. It becomes more common as women get older.

Question: Jimbo liked to work out a lot, while James never worked out. Which person would have stronger muscles? Option1: Jimbo Option2: James Qualitative Statement: Muscles that are exercised are bigger and stronger than muscles that are not exercised.
Question: When we add more water to something there will be Option1: fewer reactions Option2: more reactions Qualitative Statement: More water allows more chemical reactions.

Question: A doubling of carbon atoms in a hydrocarbon will cause _____ isomers. Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: As you increase the number of carbon atoms in a hydrocarbon, the number of isomers quickly increases.

Question: If Mona is building a structure and she wants to make it more functional, what would decreasing the surface area of that structure do? Option1: increase functioning Option2: decrease functioning Qualitative Statement: In Life Sciences it is important to note that whenever a structure has an increased surface area, there is an increase in the functioning of that structure.

Question: Water near shore will have _____ dissolved nutrients than water further away shore. Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: Therefore, water nearer shore usually contains more dissolved nutrients than water farther from shore.

Question: Would you expect to see greater allele shift in a population of roses grown in a greenhouse if the greenhouse had Option1: 20 rose plants Option2: 2,000 rose plants? Qualitative Statement: The smaller a population is, the more allele frequencies may drift.

Question: If the speed of a stream decreases, the size of the particles carried in that stream Option1: increase Option2: decrease Qualitative Statement: In erosion, a slower moving stream will only carry smaller particles.

Question: Ian wants to be able to see the most light coming from the stars at night, so the telescope that he will use will be Option1: larger Option2: smaller Qualitative Statement: Larger telescopes can collect more light.

Question: If a substance is tested and has low a pH of 1 we could say that the substance is Option1: acidic Option2: basic Qualitative Statement: For bases we can state the folllowing: The higher the pH of a substance, the more basic it is.

Question: Between a marble and a cannon ball, both travelling at the same speed, the object with the greater momentum would be Option1: the cannon ball Option2: the marble? Qualitative Statement: The more mass a moving object has or the faster its moving, the greater its momentum.
Question: The waves in the ocean are tall meaning they have a _____ amplitude. Option1: high Option2: low Qualitative Statement: The higher the crests of a wave are, the greater the amplitude.

Question: If there are more bacteria with the right mutation, will the occurrence of the mutation become Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: Bacteria with a mutation the helps resist antibiotics increase in numbers, so the mutation becomes more common.

Question: Eric added branching isomers to one solution, and left the other solution alone. The isomer solution now has a _____ boiling point. Option1: lower Option2: higher Qualitative Statement: The more branching there is in isomers, the lower the boiling and melting points are.

Question: If Mary is running and race and begins to breathe hard, what happens to the air pressure in her lungs as she expands her chest? Option1: increases Option2: decreases Qualitative Statement: Exhaling, or breathing out, decreases the size of the chest, which increases air pressure inside the lungs.

Question: If Mona is building an electrical machine and she decreases the length of the wire feeding power to it, what happens to the resistance of that wire? Option1: increases Option2: decreases Qualitative Statement: Longer wires have more resistance than shorter wires.

Question: James left a pot of water in the refrigerator. As the water started to cool down, what would happen to the rate of evaporation? Option1: increase Option2: decrease Qualitative Statement: In transipration, at warmer temperatures water molecules move faster, and the rate of evaporation from stomata is therefore much faster.

Question: A smaller amount of force has _____ acceleration than a large amount of force Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: The smaller its mass is, the greater its acceleration for a given amount of force.
Question: Sue weighs 50kg while Tom weighs 100kg, who has less gravity? Option1: Sue Option2: Tom Qualitative Statement: Less massive objects also have less gravity than more massive objects.

Question: Rick had a rock (Rock A) from 1000 feet beneath the crust's surface. He later dug 3000 feet deeper and got a second rock (Rock B). Which rock is likely older? Option1: Rock A Option2: Rock B Qualitative Statement: Older rocks are at the bottom and younger rocks are at the top.
Question: Someone that has very little energy will be Option1: slow Option2: fast Qualitative Statement: The more energy the particles in matter have, the faster and more strongly they vibrate.

Question: Ann and Bob were both farmers. Ann lived in a warm climate while Bob lived in a colder climate. When they compared notes they found that the number of crops they could successfully grow was different. Who's farm would be able to grow more types of crops? Option1: Bob Option2: Ann Qualitative Statement: The warmer a climate is, the more types of vegetation it will have and the greater the rate of biological weathering.

Question: John was watching the particle accelerator and made an observation. The lesser an objects mass and velocity, the kinetic energy was Option1: Greater Option2: Less Qualitative Statement: An object with greater mass or greater velocity has more kinetic energy.

Question: Tina is drinking water. Tina blows slowly on the surface of the water. The faster she blows, the _____ the waves are. Option1: smaller Option2: bigger Qualitative Statement: The faster, longer, and farther the wind blows, the bigger the waves are.

Question: Milo is flying a rocket in the mesosphere. If he increases his altitude, what happens to the temperature? Option1: increases Option2: decreases Qualitative Statement: In the mesosphere, temperature decreases as altitude increases.

Question: If Mona is a nursing mother and her body begins producing less prolactin then before, what happens to the amount of milk she will produce? Option1: decrease Option2: increase Qualitative Statement: The more the baby suckles, the more prolactin is released, which causes more milk to be produced.

Question: The farther that water gets from the shore the _____ nutrients there are. Option1: more Option2: fewer Qualitative Statement: Most nutrients are washed into ocean water from land. Therefore, water closer to shore tends to have more nutrients.

Question: Planets moving closer together will have _____ magnetic attraction. Option1: less Option2: more Qualitative Statement: As the distance between the objects increases the magnetic force of attraction decreases.

Question: Mike is stretching a rubber band out. The harder he pulls, and the more he stretches it, the resistance of the band is Option1: greater Option2: lesser Qualitative Statement: The farther you stretch the band, the greater the resistance is.

Question: As waves get smaller the frequency of them Option1: increases Option2: decreases Qualitative Statement: Wave frequency can be measured by counting the number of crests or compressions that pass the point in 1 second or other time period. The higher the number is, the greater is the frequency of the wave.

Question: Donna is noting that the atmosphere doesn't seem very dense where she's visiting, so compared to her home she must be at an altitude that is Option1: higher Option2: lower Qualitative Statement: The density of the atmosphere decreases with an increase in the height above sea level (altitude).

Question: Tasha is studying birth rates in various countries. She looks at two countries. In South Africa, the food supply is currently higher than in Australia. Because of this, the birth rate in South Africa, compared to Australia, will be Option1: lower Option2: higher Qualitative Statement: Low food supply or a lack of space can lower birth rates, increase death rates, or lead to emigration.

Question: If Mona sells her electric car and switches to a gas car, what will happen to the amount of pollution she produces? Option1: increase Option2: decrease Qualitative Statement: Plug-in hybrids run for a longer time on electricity and so are less polluting than regular hybrids.

Question: Mike needed to get a dark picture . In order to get the darkest photo, Mike made the exposure Option1: longer Option2: shorter Qualitative Statement: The longer the exposure, the more light that the telescope can gather to make the image.

Question: David spent a lot of money to buy tons of things for his house, but he ended up with a lot of things that were Option1: wasted Option2: saved Qualitative Statement: Increased resource use generally means more waste; electronic waste from developed nations is a growing problem in the developing world.
Question: Timmy tested his chemicals by subtracting water and noticed _____ reactions. Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: More water allows more chemical reactions.

Question: Theresa made a device that uses 25% of usable energy. Ryan made a device that uses 10% of usable energy. _____ made a device that is less efficient. Option1: Theresa Option2: Ryan Qualitative Statement: The more efficient a device is, the greater the percentage of usable energy it produces.

Question: Dilbert had a well that he used since he was a child that filled up. This likely occurred because the water table Option1: rose Option2: dropped Qualitative Statement: As the water is pumped out, the water table slowly falls, requiring wells to be dug deeper, which takes more money and energy.

Question: Compared to the Sun, which is an average star, would star WR 102, which is the hottest known star, be Option1: brighter than the Sun Option2: dimmer than the Sun? Qualitative Statement: The hotter a main sequence star is, the brighter it is.
Question: If Jon subtracts more weight from his car, he will need to use _____ energy. Option1: less Option2: more Qualitative Statement: Lighter, more streamlined vehicles need less energy.

Question: In ancient times, there was worse medicine. This means there was a _____ death rate. Option1: lower Option2: higher Qualitative Statement: More recently, the death rate has fallen because of the availability of more food and medical advances.

Question: Milo works as an astronomer and he has multiple telescopes at his disposal. If he is looking at the stars through a large telescope and then moves to a smaller one, will the amount of light collected by the smaller one be Option1: greater Option2: smaller Qualitative Statement: Larger telescopes can collect more light.

Question: Reid notices changes in the weather and temperature from 100 years ago. This likely was caused by _____ greenhouse gas levels. Option1: increased Option2: decreased Qualitative Statement: As greenhouse gases increase, changes will be more extreme.

Question: A vehicle that was sleek and aerodynamic and a vehicle that was bulky were each driven the same distance over the same amount of time. Which vehicle needed to more energy to power it? Option1: bulky vehicle Option2: sleek vehicle Qualitative Statement: Lighter, more streamlined vehicles need less energy.

Question: If Mona increases the density of her water by adding chemicals to it, what happens to the space it takes up inside of her pesticide bottle? Option1: increases Option2: decreases Qualitative Statement: More dense water takes up less space than less dense water.

Question: Reid has a very fit genotype. If he compares this genotype to an even more fit genotype, his would be more likely to pass _____ copies of their alleles down. Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: Genotypes with greater fitness produce more offspring and pass more copies of their alleles to the next generation.

Question: John was analyzing some of the results from his sunscreen study. He found that a higher SPF protects the skin Option1: Shorter Option2: Longer Qualitative Statement: A sunscreen with a higher SPF value protects the skin longer.

Question: If Mona is excavating an archeological site and she discovers some fossils near the surface then compares them to fossils she found deeper down, which fossils will be older? Option1: near the surface Option2: deeper down Qualitative Statement: Lower rock layers were laid down earlier, so they are assumed to contain older fossils.

Question: Would Jim's solution become more or less acidic if he increased the concentration of hydrogen atoms in it? Option1: more acidic Option2: less acidic Qualitative Statement: With a higher the concentration of hydrogen ions, a solution is more acidic and has a lower pH.

Question: Tim has a quark and pulls it closer to Rob, who also has a quark. What happens to the attraction force between the quarks? Option1: it increases Option2: it decreases Qualitative Statement: Gluons make quarks attract each other more strongly the farther apart the quarks get.

Question: If Jim increases the amount of field lines drawn what will happen to the strength of the field? Option1: decrease Option2: increase Qualitative Statement: The more field lines that are drawn, the stronger the field.

Question: Rachel was looking into the night sky. The darkest star is most likely: Option1: the hottest Option2: the coldest Qualitative Statement: The hotter a main sequence star is, the brighter it is.

Question: If someone has a smaller than average physical heart then it will beat _____ in order to pump blood. Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: When the heart expels more blood with each stroke, the heart has to beat less often in order to maintain the same volume of blood flow.

Question: Jill had two wires in her lab, one was half the thickness of the other and she measured the resistance of each. She saw that the _____ one showed less resistance. Option1: thicker Option2: thinner Qualitative Statement: Thicker wires offer less resistance.

Question: When observing reactants and their particles, Shane decreases the temperature they're exposed to, noting that they now move Option1: faster Option2: slower Qualitative Statement: At higher temperatures, particles of reactants have more energy, so they move faster.

Question: Going lower into the thermosphere will result in finding _____ temperatures. Option1: higher Option2: lower Qualitative Statement: In the thermosphere, temperatures increase as altitude increases.

Question: Johnny was was playing with chalk outside. His mom called him in for lunch, while he was inside his red chalk sat in the sun, and his blue chalk was in the shade. When Johnny returned outside and picked up the red and blue which had a higher temperature? Option1: the red chalk Option2: the blue chalk Qualitative Statement: If two objects have the same mass, the object with the higher temperature has greater thermal energy.

Question: Karen is feeling very cool, and starts to chill. Her blood flow is decreased, likely because the day is Option1: hot Option2: cold Qualitative Statement: On a hot day, an endotherm may give off more heat by increasing blood flow to the surface of the body.

Question: A particle with more energy will vibrate _____ than one with less energy. Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: The more energy the particles in matter have, the faster and more strongly they vibrate.

Question: If Mona is comparing sandpaper with notebook paper and she determines that sandpaper is rougher then notebook paper, which object has more friction? Option1: sandpaper Option2: notebook paper Qualitative Statement: Rougher surfaces have more friction between them than smoother surfaces.

Question: Rocks that are buried very shallow are _____ than rocks on the surface. Option1: newer Option2: older Qualitative Statement: The main law is the law of superposition. This law states that deeper rock layers are older than layers closer to the surface.

Question: Eric hears a sound from far away. If this is the first sound he heard, this sound is likely Option1: strong Option2: weak Qualitative Statement: The farther the sound waves travel away from the source, the more spread out their energy becomes.

Question: If Mona is playing with a rubber band and she stretches it out, what happens to the amount of elastic force contained in the rubber band? Option1: increases Option2: decreases Qualitative Statement: The elastic force increases the more the material is stretched or compressed.

Question: Jim's skin was noticeably darker than his friend Matt's skin. This means that _____ produces more melanin. Option1: Jim Option2: Matt Qualitative Statement: However, the melanocytes of people with darker skin produce more melanin.

Question: If Mona is in her sailboat and she takes a sample of the water far away from shore to test for nutrients and compares it to sample that she took while close to the shore, which sample will have more nutrients? Option1: close to shore Option2: far from shore Qualitative Statement: Most nutrients are washed into ocean water from land. Therefore, water closer to shore tends to have more nutrients.

Question: If Jim loses a lot of blood from a cut he sustains, what will happen to his blood pressure? Option1: it will become lower Option2: it will become higher Qualitative Statement: If blood volume in the body decreases, blood pressure decreases.

Question: If Milo places his coffee into the microwave and heats it up, what will happen to the rate of vibration of the molecules in the drink? Option1: increase Option2: decrease Qualitative Statement: Warmer molecules vibrate faster than cooler ones.

Question: John was weighing some materials in his science lab. He observed that as objects had lower density, the heaviness of the objects Option1: Increased Option2: Decreased Qualitative Statement: A given volume of a denser substance is heavier than the same volume of a less dense substance.

Question: Sally is pulling two wagons. The red wagon is full of sand, and the blue wagon is empty. The wagon that will be more difficult to pull is the Option1: red wagon Option2: blue wagon Qualitative Statement: The full box is harder to move because it has greater mass and therefore greater inertia.

Question: Donald is elderly, and Shane is young. Donald's risk of cardiovascular diseases, compared to Shane's is Option1: greater Option2: lesser Qualitative Statement: Older age, male gender, and a family history of cardiovascular disease all increase the risk of developing cardiovascular diseases and cant be controlled.

Question: If Mona fills up a cup with water and places that water into the freezer, what happens to the density of the water as it cools down? Option1: increases Option2: decreases Qualitative Statement: When a volume of water is cooled, the molecules move less vigorously, so same number of molecules takes up less space and the water is denser.

Question: Shane wants a field that is very weak. In order do achieve this goal, Shane needs to draw Option1: less field lines Option2: more field lines Qualitative Statement: The more field lines that are drawn, the stronger the field.

Question: A very inefficient pair of solar panels will produce Option1: little energy Option2: a lot of energy Qualitative Statement: The more efficient a device is, the greater the percentage of usable energy it produces.

Question: As computers have made work easier for people we have had to do Option1: more work Option2: less work. Qualitative Statement: More advanced farming practices allowed a single farmer to grow food for many more people.

Question: If Jim starts exercising and performs more anaerobic exercises, would his muscles get Option1: bigger Option2: smaller Qualitative Statement: Anaerobic exercises cause muscles to get bigger and stronger.

Question: Bob's blood glucose levels have increased, which means he should also be producing _____ insulin. Option1: less Option2: more Qualitative Statement: As blood glucose levels decrease, less insulin is produced.

Question: If America is a poor nation and China is a rich nation, then America's energy usage compared to China's is Option1: greater Option2: smaller Qualitative Statement: People in the richer nations of the world use far more energy, especially energy from fossil fuels, than people in the poorer nations do.
Question: Fran stayed indoors while Geremy went in the sun. Who is more likely to get skin cancer? Option1: Fran Option2: Geremy Qualitative Statement: More UV rays increase skin cancer rates.
Question: The rocks that are on the surface of a volcano are Option1: young Option2: old Qualitative Statement: The upper rock layers are much younger.

Question: Compared to sound waves travelling through a cup of boiling water, would sound waves travelling through a cup of ice water move Option1: slower Option2: faster? Qualitative Statement: For a given medium, sound waves travel more slowly at lower temperatures.

Question: John was checking the temperature of the unit. He saw that as the temperature decreased when the level of energy was Option1: Greater Option2: Lesser Qualitative Statement: The temperature of matter increases with the added energy.

Question: If Earth's temperature were to increase, there would be _____ glaciers. Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: The glaciers on Earth are getting smaller and smaller as Earths temperature rises.

Question: When we stretch a rubber band to a larger size it gets tough meaning it has Option1: more resistance Option2: less resistance Qualitative Statement: The farther you stretch the band, the greater the resistance is.

Question: Dan is pulling his car up a hill, and wants to pull it with as little force as possible. In order to do this effectively, Dan will need to use how many rope segments Option1: less Option2: more Qualitative Statement: The more rope segments on a pully that are helping to do the lifting work, the less force that is needed for the job.

Question: Jill was watching her baby as she was breastfeeding it. She noticed that the more that the baby suckled, the amount of prolactin released became Option1: Greater Option2: Lesser Qualitative Statement: The more the baby suckles, the more prolactin is released, which causes more milk to be produced.

Question: Peter found a cool rock right under the surface of some dirt. He knew the rock was _____. Option1: older Option2: younger Qualitative Statement: Fossils found at the lowest layer of rock would be the oldest, as these would have been buried for the longest time, whereas fossils found closer to the surface would be buried more recently and therefore be younger.

Question: When we look at monkeys and humans they have a little matching DNA meaning they are. Option1: similar Option2: very different Qualitative Statement: The more similar the DNA molecules of different species are, the closer the relationship is likely to be.

Question: A group of settlers decided to live close to one aquifer instead of another aquifer because the aquifer they chose was much closer to the surface. Getting water from the aquifer closer to the surface will be Option1: easier Option2: more difficult. Qualitative Statement: The closer to the surface an aquifer is, the easier it is to get the water.

Question: Ian is looking at quarks and sees that they are not attracted to each other. Ian knows that the distance between the quarks is currently Option1: close Option2: distant Qualitative Statement: Gluons make quarks attract each other more strongly the farther apart the quarks get.

Question: Two friends are headed to the beach, Mike and John. Mike is white, and John is black. Both want to make the same amount of vitamin D through sun exposure. The person who will take less time to make the amount of vitamin D is Option1: Mike Option2: John Qualitative Statement: Pigments in the skin act like a filter that can prevent the skin from making vitamin D. As a result, people with darker skin need more time in the sun than people with lighter skin to make the same amount of vitamin D.

Question: Linnie played with a rubber band by pulling at it with her hands. The more she pulled it apart, the _____ the force. Option1: weaker Option2: stronger Qualitative Statement: The farther apart you move your hands, the stronger the force of the rubber band pulling your hands together.

Question: As Cindy swam closer to the ocean surface, it got lighter and _____. Option1: warmer Option2: cooler Qualitative Statement: Water density increases as salinity and pressure increase, or as temperature decreases.

Question: Rita and Ira are identical twins of the same size. If Ira is a higher temperature, who has greater thermal energy? Option1: Rita Option2: Ira Qualitative Statement: If two objects have the same mass, the object with the higher temperature has greater thermal energy.
Question: When ice melts into water it becomes Option1: less dense. Option2: more dense Qualitative Statement: Water becomes more dense when it is colder and when it has more salt.

Question: Mary is taking measurements of the amount of oxygen in samples of water. If she measured the total levels of dissolved oxygen in a sample at 70 degrees fahrenheit and compared it to a sample at 80 degrees fahrenheit, which would contain more dissolved oxygen? Option1: 80 degrees fahrenheit Option2: 70 degrees fahrenheit Qualitative Statement: Warm water cant hold as much dissolved oxygen as cool water, so an increase in the temperature of water decreases the amount of oxygen it contains.

Question: What will happen to the amount of elastic potential energy in Jim's rubber band if he expands it? Option1: more potential energy Option2: less potential energy Qualitative Statement: The more an elastic object is stretched or compressed, the greater its elastic potential energy is.

Question: When you are talking to someone in the desert the sound will travel Option1: faster Option2: slower Qualitative Statement: For a given medium such as air, sound has a slower speed at lower temperatures.

Question: Milo has been growing his nails out for a very long time. As his nails get longer, what happens to the amount of cells added to them? Option1: increase Option2: decrease Qualitative Statement: As the nail grows, more cells are added at the nail bed.

Question: Carter buries cans of soda in the dirt. The deeper the holes for the cans of soda, the pressure will be Option1: lesser Option2: greater Qualitative Statement: As the rocks move deeper into the Earth, temperature and pressure increase.

Question: If Mona is a smoker, but decides to stop smoking, what happens to the difficulty her lungs experience in removing chemicals from the air? Option1: increase Option2: decrease Qualitative Statement: When a person smokes there are chemicals released by the tobacco that enter the lungs. Because the lungs have to work harder to remove the chemicals, the body has to work harder to get the air needed to survive.

Question: If Mona is comparing two species and she notices that their DNA molecules are more similar, what does that tell her about the species relationship? Option1: distance relationship Option2: close relationship Qualitative Statement: The more similar the DNA molecules of different species are, the closer the relationship is likely to be.

Question: What happens to a light car when it has the same power as a heavy car? Option1: accelerates faster Option2: accelerates slower Qualitative Statement: The smaller its mass is, the greater its acceleration for a given amount of force.

Question: Tanya has a substance with mass 10kg. Logan has a substance with mass 5kg. If both substances are the same size, who has the denser substance. Option1: Tanya Option2: Logan Qualitative Statement: If we have two materials with the same volume, the material with a higher mass will be more dense.

Question: The reason scientists use huge telescopes is because they collect Option1: more light Option2: less light Qualitative Statement: Larger telescopes can collect more light and see finer details than smaller telescopes.

Question: Lana is noting that the wind lately has been very strong. Lana can now tell that the air pressures over the Earth's surface have had differences that are Option1: greater Option2: lesser Qualitative Statement: Differences in air pressure over the surface of the Earth result in wind. The greater the differences in air pressures, the stronger the wind.

Question: Shane wants to get the least resistance out of his wire for his computer, so he gets a wire that is Option1: thicker Option2: thinner Qualitative Statement: The thinner the wire, the more resistance it offers.

Question: If Jim turns the thermostat up in his room while listening to music, what will happen to the speed of the sound waves in the room? Option1: they will speed up Option2: they will slow down Qualitative Statement: For a given medium, sound has a slower speed at lower temperatures.

Question: Dave was looking lenses for his new digital camera. He saw on the specifications that the less curved the lens is, the amount of light refracted Option1: increases Option2: decreases Qualitative Statement: The more curved the surface of a lens is, the more it refracts light.

Question: If Mona is flying her plane in the stratosphere on a journey and she moves lower in the stratosphere, what happens to the temperatures her plane experiences? Option1: they increase Option2: they decrease Qualitative Statement: The stratosphere contains the ozone layer, the temperatures increase as altitude increases.

Question: A person is digging up rocks, and wants to get the newest ones. The person will dig Option1: deeper Option2: shallower Qualitative Statement: Older rocks are at the bottom and younger rocks are at the top.

Question: Two planets are drawn to each other in space, however they begin to drift closer over time. As the years press on, the planets will have a gravitation attraction between them that is Option1: greater Option2: lesser Qualitative Statement: As the distance between the objects increases, the force of gravitational attraction decreases.

Question: The electron levels closest to the nucleus of an atom have _____ energy than those further away. Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: As you go farther from the nucleus of an atom, the electron levels have more and more energy.

Question: Mel stops after running down the street for exercise. As Mel's heart rate decreases, Mel's blood flow Option1: decreases Option2: increases Qualitative Statement: Warming up exercises increases the blood flow to the muscles and increases the heart rate.

Question: If Mona is breathing hard and her volume decreases, what happens to the air pressure inside her lungs? Option1: increases Option2: decreases Qualitative Statement: During inhalation, because the chest volume is larger, the air pressure inside the lungs is lower than the air pressure outside.

Question: A planet with a long orbit will take _____ time to revolve around the Sun than one with a small orbit. Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: The planets further from the Sun will have bigger orbits, and therefore take longer to revolve around the Sun.

Question: If wavelengths become shorter, there will be _____ move past a particular spot. Option1: more Option2: less Qualitative Statement: This means that as wavelengths get shorter, more waves move past a particular spot in the same amount of time.

Question: When humans grow trees what happens to the population of the animals in the forest Option1: Lower Option2: Increase Qualitative Statement: The forest habitat of elephants has also decreased in size due to humans moving in, so the numbers of the elephants have decreased.

Question: A rapid increase in electricity consumption could mean _____ pollution. Option1: less Option2: more Qualitative Statement: We need to reduce our electricity consumption in order to reduce pollution.

Question: If Jim decreases the level of sound coming from his speakers it means that the time it would take for him to experience hearing loss would Option1: increase Option2: decrease Qualitative Statement: The louder the sounds are, the less exposure is needed to cause hearing loss.

Question: Since Kim has more melanin than Jennifer, when they lay out in the sun Jennifer's skin is _____ than Kim's. Option1: darker Option2: lighter Qualitative Statement: However, the melanocytes of people with darker skin produce more melanin.

Question: Donald is elderly, and Shane is young. Shane's risk of cardiovascular diseases, compared to Donald's is Option1: greater Option2: lesser Qualitative Statement: Older age, male gender, and a family history of cardiovascular disease all increase the risk of developing cardiovascular diseases and cant be controlled.

Question: If Mona is in space comparing the distance of certain planets from the Sun and she notices that Neptune is closer than Pluto, which planet will have the shorter orbit? Option1: Pluto Option2: Neptune Qualitative Statement: In general, the farther away from the Sun, the greater the distance from one planets orbit to the next.

Question: Would it require more strength for a construction worker to move a heavy load of bricks with a pulley that used Option1: 1 rope segment? Option2: 10 rope segments Qualitative Statement: The more rope segments on a pully that are helping to do the lifting work, the less force that is needed for the job.

Question: Mercury is closer to the sun than Jupiter. This means that the pull of gravity from the sun on Mercury is Option1: stronger Option2: weaker. Qualitative Statement: Objects that are closer together have a stronger force of gravity between them.

Question: Sarah is looking at layers of rock on a cliff face. She can see that the rock at the very bottom of the cliff are Option1: older Option2: younger Qualitative Statement: The upper rock layers are much younger.

Question: Mona is developing a computerized model to detect changes in weather patterns for her farming business. If she adds computing power to the computer she is using to develop the model, what happens to the chances that model will be correct? Option1: increase Option2: decrease Qualitative Statement: But the more computing power that goes into the model and the care with which the scientists construct the model can increase the chances that a model will be accurate.

Question: If we have a bag of feathers and a bag of bricks of the same volume, the lighter item will be the Option1: feathers Option2: bricks Qualitative Statement: If we have two materials with the same volume, the material with a higher mass will be more dense.

Question: As you travel below the ozone layer the temperatures become Option1: higher Option2: lower Qualitative Statement: The stratosphere contains the ozone layer, the temperatures increase as altitude increases.

Question: Steve noticed when looking at the series circuit that as more resistors were added the resistance Option1: increased Option2: decreased Qualitative Statement: In a series circuit, the resistance increases as more resistors are added in series.

Question: The pulling force of a rubber band will _____ when you move your hands together. Option1: increase Option2: decrease Qualitative Statement: The farther apart you move your hands, the stronger the force of the rubber band pulling your hands together.
